ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes I would. It's comprehensive for the one-semester format.
This course is quite comprehensive. I would recommend this to someone interested in reactors.
A very informative and rigorous class.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Not having a chemical engineering background, I feel much better versed in reactors and kinetics which I believe is the purpose of requiring the course for future chemical engineering endeavors.
My primary research is in reaction engineering, so this course was very relevant.
